<HEAD>On the Light Side</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOLLAND, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The yellow brick road leads to <LOCATION> Holland </LOCATION> this weekend, as four of the original munchkins join fans of `` The Wizard of Oz.'' Many believe the author who inspired the film classic, <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Baum </PERSON>, patterned part of <PERSON> Dorothy </PERSON>'s travels to Oz after local sites and people because he had a summer cottage in this town. `` It really reminds me of the set,'' said <PERSON> Margaret </PERSON> <PERSON> Pellegrini </PERSON>, 65, who played one of the `` Sleepyheads'' who welcomed <PERSON> Dorothy </PERSON> to Oz. <PERSON> Dorothy </PERSON> apparently was modeled after a neighbor, <PERSON> Dorothy </PERSON> <PERSON> Martindale </PERSON>, who wore her hair in pigtails and had a small dog, said festival organizer J.L. <PERSON> Landry </PERSON>. The Emerald Castle is said to be drawn from nearby Castle Park and a circle of houses called <ORGANIZATION> Perry </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Circle </ORGANIZATION> was the model for <LOCATION> Munchkinland </LOCATION>, she said. This year _ the 50th anniversary of the MGM classic _ will be especially busy, said <PERSON> Meinhardt </PERSON> <PERSON> Raabe </PERSON>, who played the coroner who pronounced the Wicked Witch of the East dead after she was crushed by <PERSON> Dorothy </PERSON>'s house. Former munchkins <PERSON> Ruth </PERSON> <PERSON> Duccini </PERSON> and <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> Ellen </PERSON> <PERSON> St. </PERSON> <PERSON> Aubin </PERSON> also appear at the festival, which runs through Sunday in this southwestern community near <LOCATION> Lake </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION>.
