early today in the Hospital of the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pennsylvania </ORGANIZATION>. The north and west walls of a three-story parking garage collapsed during the storm, damaging two parked vehicles and a nearby house, police said. Officer <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Beren </PERSON> said a sudden darkness descended while he was on patrol. `` I could n't see two feet in front of my face,'' he said. `` It was black and dark _ and then there was a roar.'' The tornado was 50 yards wide at points, the weather service said. <ORGANIZATION> Philadelphia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electric </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Wood </PERSON> said about 4,500 customers lost power for at least part of the evening. A Camden family had to be evacuated from their home after a beam crashed through the ceiling, said <PERSON> Camy </PERSON> <PERSON> Trinidad </PERSON>, a spokeswoman for the <ORGANIZATION> Camden </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Red </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cross </ORGANIZATION>.
