<HEAD>Student Leader Says Chinese Tanks `Made Pancakes' Out of Protesters</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-China, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A Chinese student leader on Saturday issued an account of the crackdown against student protests in <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> a week ago, saying it was her responsibility to tell the truth being denied in government reports. <PERSON> Cai </PERSON> <PERSON> Ling </PERSON>, who identified herself as the students' chief commander from June 2 to June 4, said in an audio recording broadcast on the CBS Evening News on Saturday that many students died and `` the executioners were the soldiers of the 27th Army.'' `` I think I'm the most qualified to talk about it, and it's my responsibility to tell everyone the truth,'' Ms. <PERSON> Ling </PERSON> said through an interpreter. She denied official <LOCATION> Chinese </LOCATION> government reports that only soldiers, not students, were killed in <LOCATION> Tiananmen </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Square </LOCATION> a week ago. Then she described the confrontation, saying many of the students did n't expect violence. `` Some students still had hopes in the government and in the soldiers. They thought, at most, that they would be carried away. They were tired and returned to their tents to sleep. `` Then the tanks made pancakes out of them. ... I do n't know the total -LRB- number of dead -RRB-, but the members of the <ORGANIZATION> Independent </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Workers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION>, on the outside, they stood their ground. And now they're all dead. `` After students left the tanks and all their personnel carriers flattened the tents with the bodies inside. Then they poured gasoline over the remains and burned them,'' she said. Thousands of students, joined by workers and others, had virtually paralyzed Chinese government operations in Tiananmen Square for several weeks before soldiers took back the area on June 3. Estimates of the number of people killed range up to 3,000. <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> said it had obtained the tape recording `` from a secret location.''
